<p class=MsoNormal>Hi,<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Is there a way to detect a situation than one of the
processes in an MPI application exits without even calling MPI_Init()? <o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>I have a case in which all the processes except one are stuck
forever in MPI_Init(), and that one exits before being able to call MPI_Init()&#8230;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>I tried using the mca params that I thought might be related
- orte_startup_timeout, orte_abort_timeout, but that didn&#8217;t help. <o:p></o:p></p>

